   INTELLIGENCE FOR MEDICINE SCIENCE, ISAIMS 2023},
Year = {2023},
Pages = {1206-1211},
Abstract = {Medical classification is a common research problem in modern medicine,
   and this paper utilizes ensemble learning techniques to improve existing
   machine learning algorithms, making them more accurate and robust.
   Taking the neonatal health status classification dataset as an example,
   classification models such as random forest, logistic regression, and
   Xgboost are applied for fitting. On the basis of a single model, the
   prediction accuracy is significantly improved by using the voting and
   stacking methods in ensemble learning. The prospect of broader
   application of ensemble learning techniques in medical AI is also
   discussed from the perspective of the volume of dataset, and possible
   ideas for the future emergence of classification models that are more
   suitable for application to medical problems are proposed.},
